%% Diagram: LAN sync — UDP discovery, mTLS HTTPS block fetch
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Client A (has block h)
    participant LAN as Local network
    participant B as Client B (needs block h)
    participant DBX as Dropbox servers

    DBX-->>A: per-namespace SSL cert (rotated on membership change)
    DBX-->>B: per-namespace SSL cert

    A->>LAN: UDP broadcast on port 17500<br/>(version, namespaces, TCP port, random ID)
    B->>LAN: UDP broadcast on port 17500
    LAN-->>A: B's broadcast
    LAN-->>B: A's broadcast

    Note over B: Need block h for namespace N

    B->>A: HEAD https://A:17500/blocks/N/h<br/>(SNI=N, mTLS with namespace cert)
    A-->>B: 200 (or 404)
    B->>A: GET https://A:17500/blocks/N/h
    A-->>B: encrypted block bytes
    B->>B: verify SHA-256 == h

    Note over B,DBX: Fall back to block server if<br/>peer unreachable / hash mismatch
